  "text_preview": "\"hard\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"hard\" The sign for \"hard\" uses \"bent-V\" hands. The dominant hand moves. The base hand does not move. In the main version, both hands are using \"bent-V\" hands. There is another version in which the base hand is a palm-down \"S-hand.\" HARD: Sample sentence: \"Do you think this class is hard?\" Here is an example of another non-dominant hand handshape that some people use with this sign. See how the left hand is in an \"S\" handshape? \"Really Hard\" Use a larger motion and more facial expression than the normal sign for hard. See: TOUGH See: DIFFICULT See: PROBLEM See: PHYSICS Want to help support ASL University? It's easy : DONATE ( Thanks! ) (You don't need a PayPal account. Just look for the credit card logos and click"
}
